":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object. Configure the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"’s or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"’s polygons collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","t